  "title": "<div>  •  The <b>power is in the ambiguity</b>, something that only comics allow",
  "content": "<div>  •  The <b>power is in the ambiguity</b>, something that only comics allow.</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>📌 <b>For Your Graphic Novel:</b><br></div>\n<div>  •  <b>What do you leave OUT?</b> Let the reader <b>connect the dots instead of showing everything.</b><br></div>\n<div>  •  <b>Use visual suggestion</b>—sometimes <b>what isn’t shown is more powerful than what is.</b><br></div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><b>3. The Six Types of Panel Transitions</b><br></div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>McCloud categorizes <b>six types of transitions</b> that <b>shape how a story unfolds visually</b> .</div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div><object><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; direction: ltr\">\n<tbody>\n<tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><div><b>Type of Transition</b></div>\n</td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><div><b>Description</b></div>\n</td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><div><b>Example</b></div>",
